Enum AminoAcid.Rotameric

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<AminoAcid.Rotameric>
      • AminoAcid.Rotameric
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<AminoAcid.Rotameric>
    Enclosing class:
    AminoAcid

    public static enum AminoAcid.Rotameric
extends java.lang.Enum<AminoAcid.Rotameric>
    Indicates whether the amino acid can be represented by standard rotamers, is non-rotameric, or contains no rotatable bonds at all. For a full description, see the Dunbrack backbone-dependent rotamer library" page.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      INVALID
      Represents an amino acid that does not have sidechain torsions.
      NON_ROTAMERIC
      Represents an amino acid that contains a terminal sp2-sp3 torsion.
      ROTAMERIC
      Represents an amino acid that has standard rotameric degrees of freedom.
